         <entry xml:id="donativa-dlgenr"
                xml:lang="en"
                type="mainEntry"
                prev="#grdwmi-dlgenr"
                next="#doqran-dlgenr"
                source="Genesis Rabbah">
            <form type="lemma" opt="false">
               <orth type="lemma" xml:lang="jpa" opt="false" select="true">דונאטיבה</orth>
               <orth type="transliteration" xml:lang="fjb" opt="false">dwnʾṭybh</orth>
               <pron notation="rabbinic" opt="false">donaʾṭivah</pron>
               <gramGrp opt="false">
                  <gram type="pos" opt="false">noun</gram>
                  <gram type="gen" opt="false">m/f</gram>
                  <gram type="num" opt="false">sg/pl</gram>
               </gramGrp>
            </form>
            <form type="variant" opt="false">
               <orth xml:lang="jpa" opt="false">דונטיבה</orth>
               <orth type="transliteration" xml:lang="fjb" opt="false">dwntybh</orth>
               <pron notation="rabbinic" opt="false">donativah</pron>
            </form>
            <form type="equivalent" xml:lang="la" opt="false">
               <quote xml:lang="la">donativa</quote>
            </form>
            <sense xml:id="donativa-dlgenr-1" opt="false">
               <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en" subtype="sense">
                  <quote>imperial donations (to the soldiers)</quote>
               </cit>
               <cit type="example">
                  <quote xml:lang="jpa">
א"ר אבא בשר ודם בשעה שהוא עושה
            <ref type="entry">אסטאטיבה</ref>
 אינו נותן
            <app>
                        <lem>דונאטיבה</lem>
                        <rdg wit="#Vat2">דינאטיבה</rdg>
                        <rdg wit="#Ox1">דונא טובה</rdg>
                        <rdg wit="#V">דונטיבא</rdg>
                        <rdg wit="#K">דונא טבא</rdg>
                     </app>
, ובשעה שהוא נותן
            <app>
                        <lem>דונאטיבה</lem>
                        <rdg wit="#Vat2">דינאטיבה</rdg>
                        <rdg wit="#Ox1">דונא טובה</rdg>
                        <rdg wit="#V">דונטיבא</rdg>
                        <rdg wit="#K">דונא טבא</rdg>
                     </app>
 אינו עושה 
            <ref type="entry">אסטאטיבה</ref>
, אבל הקדוש ברוך הוא עשה
            <ref type="entry">אסטאטיבה</ref>
 ונתן
            <app>
                        <lem>דונאטיבה</lem>
                        <rdg wit="#Vat2">דינאטיבה</rdg>
                        <rdg wit="#Ox1">דונא טובה</rdg>
                        <rdg wit="#V">דונטיבא</rdg>
                        <rdg wit="#K">דונא טבא</rdg>
                     </app>
 וישבות ויברך
         </quote>
                  <bibl default="false" status="draft">
                     <ref type="witness">10,9</ref>
                     <ref type="witness">Ι 86: 5, 6</ref>
                  </bibl>
                  <cit type="translation">
                     <quote xml:lang="en">
R. Abba said: When a mortal king puts [his army] into a permanent camp he doesn’t give donations, and when he gives donations he doesn’t put [his army] into a permanent camp. But the Holy one, blessed be He, made a stop and gave donations [as it is written]: and he rested, and he blessed.
= TanhB Wa-yeṣeʾ 22 (<term xml:lang="jpa">דונאטיבא</term>); Yalq 16 (5c: 37-39) (<term xml:lang="jpa">דונטיבא</term>)
            </quote>
                  </cit>
               </cit>
            </sense>
            <etym type="borrowing" opt="false">
               <lbl opt="false">source language</lbl>
               <lang opt="false">Latin</lang>
               <cit type="etymon" xml:lang="la">
                  <xr type="related" opt="false">
                     <lbl opt="false">Cf. Lewis / Short</lbl>
                     <ref target="http://www.perseus.tufts.edu/hopper/morph?l=d%C5%8Dn%C4%81t%C4%ABvum&amp;la=la&amp;can=d%C5%8Dn%C4%81t%C4%ABvum0"
                          type="entry">dōnātīvum</ref>
                  </xr>
               </cit>
            </etym>
            <note anchored="true">
The reading of AC III 96-97 is <term xml:lang="jpa">דונטיבא ללגיונות</term>
               <term xml:lang="fjb">dwnṭybʾ llgywnwt</term> „donations for the legions“ 
(as in NumR Nasoʾ 7,3: <term xml:lang="jpa">דונטיבא ללגיונותיו</term>
               <term xml:lang="fjb">dwntybʾ llgywnwtyw</term> „donations for his (i.e. the king’s) legions“). Cg. Levy I 384; Jastrow I 286. The reading of Vat 2 is a corruption; the readings in Ox 1 and K are an “emendation” owing to non-understanding of the word. Cf. Syr. <term xml:lang="syrc">ܕܘܢܐܛܝܒܐ</term>
               <term xml:lang="fjb">dwnʾṭybʾ</term> (Sokoloff, SL 284).
Other spellings: <term xml:lang="jpa">דונטיבא</term>
               <term xml:lang="fjb">dwnṭybʾ</term>.
   </note>
